item.title: Can Chinchillas Eat Carrots? What You Need to Know
item.description: Chinchillas are omnivores, so they can eat both meat and plants. They’re native to Western South America and live in the Andes Mountains. In their natural habitats in the wild, they mainly eat grass and seeds, along with some insects and bird eggs. As pets, chinchillas typically have access to more varieties of foods that are either scarce or nonexistent in their natural habitats. One of these foods is carrots. Although they don’t naturally grow in the Andes, carrots are safe for chinchillas to eat in moderation.
